<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14081">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Cycling.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12932">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="vimeo.com/1125028263" target="_blank"
        >Hazards, Prevention, and First Aid | Produced by Scouting America
        (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12932 mb-requirement-id-12933">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the most likely hazards you may encounter
        while participating in cycling activities and what you should do to
        anticipate, help prevent, mitigate, and respond to these hazards.
        Explain to your counselor how to ride predictably, be conspicuous, think
        ahead, and ride ready. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dcRpBP9WvKg%20" target="_blank"
          >Avoiding Road Hazards (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12932 mb-requirement-id-12934">
        (b) Show that you know first aid for injuries or illnesses that could
        occur while cycling, including cuts, scratches, concussions, blisters,
        sunburn, heat exhaustion, heatstroke, hypothermia, frostbite,
        dehydration, insect stings, tick bites, and snakebite. Explain to your
        counselor why you should be able to identify the poisonous plants and
        poisonous animals that are found in your area. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oPCWzECMD_4%20" target="_blank"
          >First Aid Guide for Mountain Bikers (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12932 mb-requirement-id-12969">
        (c) Explain the importance of wearing the right clothing and gear while
        cycling, including a properly sized and fitted helmet. Know the Scouting
        America Bike Safety Guidelines. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2TYe3APtKtc&list=PLHGEvyG5wuthKCwDfpQIZfTfan4mI6XTe&index=5%20"
          target="_blank"
          >Bike Tips: Gear to Make Your Ride More Comfortable (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T3u51W0LN2U%20" target="_blank"
          >How to Wear a Helmet (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12966">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Describe your state and local laws concerning bicycles. Discuss what is
      the same and what is different from laws applying to motor vehicles.
      Explain where and how you should ride on roads and streets to include lane
      position, changing lanes, making left and right turns, and riding through
      intersections. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://vimeo.com/1125028107" target="_blank"
        >Bicycle Laws and Safe Road Riding | Produced by Scouting America
        (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/-Jp0SSAeCiY" target="_blank"
        >Rules of the Road (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12967">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Explain the importance of wearing a properly sized and fitted helmet while
      cycling and of wearing the right clothing for the weather. Know the
      Scouting America Bike Safety Guidelines. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hLlXswx0VvQ " target="_blank"
        >Fitting a Bike Helmet (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12935">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Using a bicycle safety checklist, clean and adjust a bicycle and present
      it to your counselor for inspection. Do the following: <br /><i
        >Resource:</i
      >
      <a href="https://vimeo.com/1125028194" target="_blank"
        >Checklist, Maintenance, and Inspection | Produced by Scouting America
        (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12935 mb-requirement-id-12936">
        (a) Show points that should be checked regularly to make sure the
        bicycle is safe to ride. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://scoutlife.org/features/169458/5-things-to-check-before-every-bike-ride/"
          target="_blank"
          >5 Things to Check Before Every Bike Ride (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12935 mb-requirement-id-12937">
        (b) Show how to adjust the saddle and handlebars for a proper fit.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dsM9brngVmc&list=PLHGEvyG5wuthKCwDfpQIZfTfan4mI6XTe&index=6%20"
          target="_blank"
          >Bike Tips: Finding and Fitting the Right Bike (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jh5Zv6Dcn6k%20" target="_blank"
          >How to Set Your Bicycle Seat Height (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12935 mb-requirement-id-12938">
        (c) Show how to adjust brakes and gear shifting (derailleurs). <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7kc-CHtlQyM&list=PLHGEvyG5wuthKCwDfpQIZfTfan4mI6XTe&index=7%20"
          target="_blank"
          >Bike Tips: Proper Shifting Technique (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12935 mb-requirement-id-12939">
        (d) Show all points that need regular lubrication.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12935 mb-requirement-id-12940">
        (e) Show how to repair a flat by removing the tire, replacing or
        patching the tube, and remounting the tire. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="vimeo.com/1125028160" target="_blank"
          >Changing a Tire with Disc Brakes | Produced by Scouting America
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="vimeo.com/1125028134" target="_blank"
          >Changing a Tire with Caliper Brakes | Produced by Scouting America
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12935 mb-requirement-id-12941">
        (f) Show that the bicycle meets local laws. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-Jp0SSAeCiY%20" target="_blank"
          >Rules of the Road (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12968">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Demonstrate basic bicycle handling skills to your counselor, to include
      how to properly mount your bicycle, starting and stopping (to include
      emergency stops), riding in a straight line, turning, shifting gears,
      scanning, and signaling. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://vimeo.com/1125028294" target="_blank"
        >Mastering Handling Basic Bicycle Handling Skills | Produced by Scouting
        America (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/XMj_95C5ihk" target="_blank"
        >Bicycle Safer Journey (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/nf5WQXFvrkk" target="_blank"
        >Bike Riding Safety (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12942">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Using the Scouting America buddy system, complete all of the requirements
      for ONE of the following options: Road Biking OR Trail or Mixed Surface
      Biking. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a
        href="https://www.scouting.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Youth-Safety-Infographic-Barriers-to-Abuse-1536x1363.png "
        target="_blank"
        >Barriers to Abuse (PDF)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12942 mb-requirement-id-12943">
        A <b>Option A—Road Biking.</b> Do the following: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://vimeo.com/1125028086" target="_blank"
          >Advanced Techniques for Urban Riding | Produced by Scouting America
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12943 mb-requirement-id-12944">
        (a) Take a road safety test with your counselor and demonstrate the
        following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12944 mb-requirement-id-12945">
        (1) On an urban street with light traffic, properly execute a left turn
        from the center of the street; also demonstrate an alternate left-turn
        technique used during periods of heavy traffic. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v_hRsNHlq8M%20" target="_blank"
          >Bike Safety | Hand Signals (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://static.nhtsa.gov/nhtsa/downloads/NTI/Responsible_Walk-Bike_Activities/ComboLessons/L3Handouts/8009_HandSignals_122811_v1a.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Bike Hand Signals (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12944 mb-requirement-id-12946">
        (2) Properly execute a right turn. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v_hRsNHlq8M" target="_blank"
          >Bike Safety | Hand Signals (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12944 mb-requirement-id-12947">
        (3) Demonstrate appropriate actions at a right-turn-only lane when you
        are continuing straight. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v_hRsNHlq8M" target="_blank"
          >Bike Safety | Hand Signals (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12944 mb-requirement-id-12948">
        (4) Show proper curbside and road-edge riding. Show how to ride safely
        along a row of parked cars. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v_hRsNHlq8M" target="_blank"
          >Bike Safety | Hand Signals (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12944 mb-requirement-id-12949">
        (5) Cross railroad tracks properly. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=62jc3-6Jgdw%20" target="_blank"
          >How to Cross Railroad Tracks (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12943 mb-requirement-id-12953">
        (b) Avoiding main highways, take two rides of 10 miles each, two rides
        of 15 miles each, and two rides of 25 miles each. You must make a report
        of the rides taken. List dates for the routes traveled, and interesting
        things seen on the ride. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.nhtsa.gov/sites/nhtsa.gov/files/bikabilitychecklist1.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Bikeability Checklist (PDF)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.mapmyride.com/" target="_blank"
          >MapMyRide (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12943 mb-requirement-id-12950">
        (c) After completing requirement b for the road biking option, do ONE of
        the following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12950 mb-requirement-id-12951">
        (1) Lay out on a road map a 50-mile trip. Stay away from main highways.
        Using your map, make this ride in eight hours or less. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://www.mapmyride.com/" target="_blank"
          >MapMyRide (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12950 mb-requirement-id-12952">
        (2) Participate in an organized bike tour of at least 50 miles. Make
        this ride in eight hours or less. Afterward, use the tour's cue sheet to
        make a map of the ride. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://lifeisabeautifuldetail.com/blog/cue-sheets"
          target="_blank"
          >Cue Sheets (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12942 mb-requirement-id-12954">
        B <b>Option B—Trail or Mixed Surface Biking. </b> Do the following:<br />
        <br /><b>Note: </b> These requirements may be completed using a mountain
        bike or other properly equipped, manually-powered cycle such as a gravel
        bike, tandem bike, hand-powered bike, recumbent bike, adult tricycle, or
        adaptive cycle. If a tandem bike is used, the Scout must actively power
        the cycle in concert with the other rider.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12954 mb-requirement-id-12955">
        (a) Demonstrate the following mountain bike handling skills to your
        counselor:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12955 mb-requirement-id-12956">
        (1) Neutral position, ready position, bike body separation (side to
        side, and forward and back), and body positioning for cornering <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/UCWu6zXDjXM?si=akxjbkFYRrChevnX"
          target="_blank"
          >The Basics of Cornering: Berms and Flat Corners (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ammz64zxnhg%20" target="_blank"
          >Advanced MTB Cornering Techniques: Body Position &amp; Technical
          Terrain (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12955 mb-requirement-id-12957">
        (2) Show shifting skills as applicable to climbs and obstacles. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7kc-CHtlQyM&list=PLHGEvyG5wuthKCwDfpQIZfTfan4mI6XTe&index=7%20"
          target="_blank"
          >Bike Tips: Proper Shifting Technique (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12955 mb-requirement-id-12958">
        (3) Show proper technique for riding up (seated, crouched, and standing)
        and down hills. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/aDwqM_ZVSUg?si=5RolaSMGLshbWZzS"
          target="_blank"
          >Make Climbing Easier With Proper Body Position (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rd-wFxmXmsM%20" target="_blank"
          >Steep &amp; Technical Climbs Made Easy With Proper Gearing &amp;
          Choice of Line (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4knf7exmrAQ%20" target="_blank"
          >How to Climb Any Hill on Your Mountain Bike (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k6ewOO9rXXY%20" target="_blank"
          >Don't Make These Common Climbing Mistakes (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12954 mb-requirement-id-12959">
        (b) Take a trail safety test with your counselor and demonstrate the
        following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12959 mb-requirement-id-12960">
        (1) Show proper trail etiquette to hikers and other cyclists, including
        when to yield the right-of-way.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12959 mb-requirement-id-12961">
        (2) Demonstrate how to correctly cross an obstacle by either going over
        the obstacle on your bike or dismounting your bike and crossing over or
        around the obstacle <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Hp_jDNN6XfQ" target="_blank"
          >How to Jump a Log on a Mountain Bike (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12959 mb-requirement-id-12962">
        (3) Cross rocks, gravel, and roots properly <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Hp_jDNN6XfQ" target="_blank"
          >How to Jump a Log on a Mountain Bike (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12954 mb-requirement-id-12963">
        (c) Describe the rules of trail riding, including how to know when a
        trail is unsuitable for riding.<br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://trailetiquette.org/" target="_blank"
          >Sharing Our Trails (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.tfnu.org/trail-etiquette/" target="_blank"
          >Trail Manners (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://treadlightly.org/learn/recreation-tips/sharing-our-trails/%20"
          target="_blank"
          >Tread Lightly (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12954 mb-requirement-id-12964">
        (d) On mountain biking or multi-use trails approved by your counselor,
        take two rides of 2 miles each, two rides of 5 miles each, and two rides
        of 8 miles each. You must make a report of the rides taken. List dates
        for the routes traveled, and interesting things seen. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://www.mapmyride.com/" target="_blank"
          >MapMyRide (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12954 mb-requirement-id-12965">
        (e) After fulfilling the previous requirement, lay out on a trail map a
        22-mile trip. You may include multiple trail systems, if needed. Stay
        away from main highways. Using your map, complete this ride in one day.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.mapmyride.com/" target="_blank"
          >MapMyRide (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
